originalText.text: This man almost killed my mother with his malpractice and negligence. He's a fool who clearly doesn't understand the chemistry of the brain and caused severe reactions to occur in my mother while she was seeing him. Not once, not twice, but three times did he put her in an emergency situation due to prescribing the wrong meds and causing her liver and thyroid to go out of control. When we went to reach him by phone, there was no answer very time and it always took days for him to get back to us. This man should have his license taken from him and be ashamed of himself as a person who took an oath as a doctor to help others. Shame on you, karma will get you.

originalText.text: Dr. Papp saved my life – several times! When I got out of a hospital in NJ and NO OTHER psychiatrist in NYC would see me, Dr. Papp made sure my meds were corrected and worked with me over a period of time to titrate them to to the most tolerable level. He is a level-headed professional, an excellent psychopharmacologist , and a compassionate person.
